&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CARDIFF&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; AND VALE &lt;strong&gt;UNIVERSITY HEALTH BOARD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialty Doctor in General Adult Psychiatry (10 sessions) Vale Locality&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for an enthusiastic and well motivated Specialty Doctor in Adult Psychiatry to work in the Hamadryad community mental health team supporting service users to participate in recovery focussed engagement with Mental Health Services. This is a primarily community focussed role based in a purpose built team and would support a multidisciplinary team including a consultant psychiatrist. Clinic and community (service users home) based work would be required. Opportunities for career and professional development are available as are possibilities to develop a special interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a teaching health board with close links to Cardiff University. The University boasts a high profile teaching, research and development role within the UK and abroad. Together we are training the next generation of medical professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;References will be required to cover a minimum of three years of previous employment and/or training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In view of Border Immigration Agency regulations, all applicants must state their current immigration status including expiry dates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A satisfactory disclosure check will be required of the successful applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
